340 g Pork Tenderloin
¾ cup Parboiled Rice
113 g Sugar Snap Peas
1 unit(s) Carrot
2 tbsp Fig Spread
1 tbsp Chicken Stock Powder
1 tbsp Zesty Garlic Blend
1 unit(s) Zucchini
2 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
½ tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Add stock powder, 1 1/4 cups (2 1/2 cups) water, and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter to a medium pot. Cover and bring to a boil over high heat.
Once boiling, add rice, then reduce heat to low. Cover and cook until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, 16-18 min.
Remove from heat. Set aside, still covered.

Peel, then quarter carrot lengthwise. Cut into 1/4-inch quarter-moons.
Halve zucchini lengthwise, then cut into 1/4-inch half-moons.
Trim sugar snap peas.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
While the pan heats, pat pork tenderloin dry with paper towels. Season with half the Zesty Garlic Blend, salt and pepper.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then pork. Pan-fry until golden on all sides, 6-8 min, then transfer pork to a foil-lined baking sheet. Reserve fat in the pan.
Spread fig spread over pork tenderloin.
Broil in the middle of the oven until lightly charred and cooked through, 14-18 min.**

While pork broils, reheat the same pan over medium.
Add carrots, zucchini, remaining Zesty Garlic Blend and 1/3 cup (1/2 cup) water. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring often, until liquid has abosrbed and veggies begin to soften, 2-4 min.
Add snap peas, and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter. Season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring often, until butter is melted and veggies are tender-crisp, 1-2 min.

Fluff rice with a fork.
Thinly slice pork.
Divide rice, pork and veggies between plates.
Pour any pork juices from baking dish over rice, if desired.

If you've opted to get pork tenderloin, sear it in the same way the recipe instructs you to sear the pork chops. Increase sear time to 6-8 min, then increase the broil time to 14-18-min.**

Thinly slice pork before dividing between plates.